  "test_expectation": [
    "The same biome can feel easier or harder depending on Atlas region, because hostile mobs receive region tags/effects when they spawn near a player.",
    "Difficulty no longer ramps just because time has passed or a chunk has existed longer.",
    "Daytime enemies should be mostly daylight-safe modded mobs from the active In Control spawner pools.",
    "Hearthlands should still be playable for early co-op, while diagonal frontier and outer regions should feel noticeably harsher."
  ]
